1
00:00:02,349 --> 00:00:06,639
There is one Spanish mystic

2
00:00:07,314 --> 00:00:09,764
named Miguel de Unamuno.

3
00:00:10,334 --> 00:00:15,284
He once said about science,

4
00:00:15,284 --> 00:00:20,217
that to study something,
it has to kill it.

5
00:00:20,217 --> 00:00:24,133
It kills something,
and then it starts studying it,

6
00:00:24,133 --> 00:00:28,003
and making so many conclusions
based upon discovery.

7
00:00:28,141 --> 00:00:32,007
[Soul | The Question of Faith]

8
00:00:32,007 --> 00:00:35,134
But what is obvious, is that

9
00:00:35,134 --> 00:00:39,764
the most essential aspect
of what was animating,

10
00:00:39,764 --> 00:00:43,478
illuminating that form,

11
00:00:43,498 --> 00:00:45,478
is no longer there.

12
00:00:45,522 --> 00:00:51,642
So, you’re studying
a dead body in a laboratory.

13
00:00:51,665 --> 00:00:56,459
So, often Śrīla Guru Maharāj,

14
00:00:56,459 --> 00:01:01,299
when he would be fielding
different questions—

15
00:01:01,299 --> 00:01:04,178
we were asking 
so many questions,

16
00:01:04,178 --> 00:01:06,728
the group of devotees—

17
00:01:09,174 --> 00:01:12,599
sometimes he would
caution us by saying,

18
00:01:12,599 --> 00:01:17,619
“We are not studying a dead body
in a laboratory,

19
00:01:18,021 --> 00:01:20,414
but we are studying something
that is living,

20
00:01:20,414 --> 00:01:22,994
and growing, and developing.”

21
00:01:23,528 --> 00:01:26,200
We hear in the early part
of the Gītā,

22
00:01:26,200 --> 00:01:30,312
second chapter, in ātma-jñān,
the famous śloka,

23
00:01:30,312 --> 00:01:34,612
dehino ’smin yathā dehe
kaumāraṁ yauvanaṁ jarā

24
00:01:34,612 --> 00:01:40,962
tathā dehāntara-prāptir
dhīras tatra na muhyati
[Bg: 2.13]

25
00:01:40,962 --> 00:01:42,210
I find it interesting.

26
00:01:42,210 --> 00:01:46,150
Kṛṣṇa is giving us 
a very simple example.

27
00:01:47,282 --> 00:01:49,152
He’s Kṛṣṇa—

28
00:01:49,152 --> 00:01:52,908
if He wanted to give
some very complicated,

29
00:01:52,908 --> 00:01:55,538
sophisticated example,

30
00:01:55,538 --> 00:01:57,435
He can do that.

31
00:01:57,435 --> 00:02:00,345
He’s Kṛṣṇa—by His expansion
as Paramātmā,

32
00:02:00,345 --> 00:02:03,485
He’s situated in the heart 
of every living being.

33
00:02:03,485 --> 00:02:06,457
So we could say, 
we could make a case, that

34
00:02:06,457 --> 00:02:09,877
if He is going
to give an example,

35
00:02:09,877 --> 00:02:12,934
it’s a good one.

36
00:02:13,290 --> 00:02:14,297
Sometimes we think,

37
00:02:14,297 --> 00:02:16,962
“What should you say 
to people in the beginning,
 

38
00:02:16,962 --> 00:02:21,147
that trying to give them
the right idea, or the right concept?”

39
00:02:21,155 --> 00:02:25,043
Well, let’s ask Kṛṣṇa!

40
00:02:25,043 --> 00:02:26,683
“What would You say?”

41
00:02:26,693 --> 00:02:28,975
—“Well, I’ve said 
in Bhagavad-gītā,

42
00:02:28,975 --> 00:02:33,855
dehino ’smin yathā dehe
kaumāraṁ yauvanaṁ jarā
[Bg: 2.13]

43
00:02:33,855 --> 00:02:37,013
It’s one of the examples
He gives there,

44
00:02:37,013 --> 00:02:39,535
talking about these
different stages

45
00:02:39,535 --> 00:02:42,303
of development of the body,

46
00:02:42,303 --> 00:02:44,217
but what is constant 
throughout—

47
00:02:44,217 --> 00:02:47,397
the atomic constant—
is the soul.

48
00:02:47,749 --> 00:02:50,549
He is saying, 
whether in the embryo,

49
00:02:50,774 --> 00:02:55,914
in a little baby,
a toddler, a child,

50
00:02:55,914 --> 00:03:01,478
a teenager, a young adult, 
adult—

51
00:03:01,778 --> 00:03:08,018
all these different bodies,
per se, are there.

52
00:03:08,309 --> 00:03:13,539
But what is constant here?
What is the atomic constant?

53
00:03:14,217 --> 00:03:16,657
Ātmā, jīvātmā.

54
00:03:16,657 --> 00:03:17,508
And then He says,

55
00:03:17,508 --> 00:03:21,898
tathā dehāntara-prāptir
dhīras tatra na muhyati
[Bg: 2.13]

56
00:03:21,942 --> 00:03:26,656
After one … And when the soul
gives up this body,

57
00:03:26,656 --> 00:03:31,085
he’ll acquire another one,
that will be based upon

58
00:03:31,085 --> 00:03:36,825
the kind of culture
of the last one.

59
00:03:37,090 --> 00:03:41,700
vāsāṁsi jīrṇāni yathā vihāya 
navāni gṛhṇāti naro ’parāṇi
[Bg: 2.22]

60
00:03:41,710 --> 00:03:44,710
Kṛṣṇa’s another example 
in the Gītā.

61
00:03:46,578 --> 00:03:51,058
He compares the body
to a garment.

62
00:03:51,060 --> 00:03:53,420
Like I noticed
on my shirt today,

63
00:03:53,465 --> 00:03:56,325
threads coming undone,
and then I thought,

64
00:03:56,325 --> 00:04:00,767
“Oh, I’ve had this shirt
for a couple of years now.”

65
00:04:00,767 --> 00:04:03,989
Then a button
will fall off, something …

66
00:04:03,989 --> 00:04:08,389
It’s like that
as you get older,

67
00:04:08,459 --> 00:04:13,787
buttons start falling off,
threads start coming undone …

68
00:04:13,787 --> 00:04:16,467
[Laughing]

69
00:04:16,577 --> 00:04:20,761
That it is a question of faith,

70
00:04:20,831 --> 00:04:25,611
because there are so many books
available in the marketplace,

71
00:04:25,611 --> 00:04:29,373
say, ‘documenting reincarnation’,

72
00:04:29,373 --> 00:04:33,313
a hundred stories that verify,
and someone says,

73
00:04:33,313 --> 00:04:38,233
“I remember in my former life ...”
Or someone woke up in England,

74
00:04:38,233 --> 00:04:41,863
and suddenly they are speaking 
perfect French and ...

75
00:04:42,168 --> 00:04:45,548
Many different types
of stories are there.

76
00:04:45,548 --> 00:04:50,000
But Guru Maharāj, he told this, 
he said, “It is a question of faith.”

77
00:04:50,000 --> 00:04:52,168
He said, 
“If someone has faith,

78
00:04:52,168 --> 00:04:56,428
then hearing a simple example—
like Kṛṣṇa’s giving in Bhagavad-gītā,

79
00:04:56,435 --> 00:04:59,697
the ‘dehino ’smin’ śloka,
‘vāsāṁsi jīrṇāni yathā vihāya’,

80
00:04:59,697 --> 00:05:01,274
and there are other
ślokas there—

81
00:05:01,274 --> 00:05:03,670
they’ll accept this,

82
00:05:03,670 --> 00:05:08,400
they’ll find it
enlightening, illuminating.

83
00:05:08,425 --> 00:05:11,935
He said, “Whereas,
if they don’t have faith,

84
00:05:12,062 --> 00:05:16,514
you can present
a mountain of evidence,

85
00:05:16,514 --> 00:05:18,785
and they won’t believe it.

86
00:05:18,785 --> 00:05:21,082
It won’t be enough for them.

87
00:05:21,082 --> 00:05:24,359
But if they have faith,
give a simple example,

88
00:05:24,359 --> 00:05:29,822
like Kṛṣṇa’s giving,
hearing that, they’ll be some ...

89
00:05:29,822 --> 00:05:35,102
It will register 
sympathetically in the heart”.

